WEBVTT

00:00:05.040 --> 00:00:06.700
Make sure to take care of yourself.

00:00:06.700 --> 00:00:08.090
I hope you find glory.

00:00:09.230 --> 00:00:11.370
I'll be waiting overseas, Kita-chan.

00:00:13.500 --> 00:00:14.490
Kita-chan?

00:00:15.320 --> 00:00:17.000
All over Japan...

00:00:17.000 --> 00:00:20.370
No, let's cause a festival
wave all over the world!

00:00:20.370 --> 00:00:22.840
Right. At the Prix de l'Arc de Triomphe.

00:00:49.440 --> 00:00:59.740
Umamusume

00:00:53.280 --> 00:00:59.740
Pretty Derby

00:02:03.490 --> 00:02:07.500
Episode 11
Decision

00:02:06.820 --> 00:02:09.480
Can't eat another bite...

00:02:09.480 --> 00:02:12.980
Not another bite...

00:02:14.790 --> 00:02:18.020
Oh, no! Dia-chan! Look how late it is!

00:02:22.810 --> 00:02:24.090
Oh, right...

00:02:24.630 --> 00:02:26.000
I better hurry.

00:02:26.000 --> 00:02:28.000
Takeshi Greengrocers

00:02:28.000 --> 00:02:30.000
There we go.

00:02:28.800 --> 00:02:30.000
Oh, honey, take care of that.

00:02:30.340 --> 00:02:32.080
Good morning!

00:02:32.080 --> 00:02:34.850
Kita-chan, you're looking lively again today.

00:02:34.850 --> 00:02:37.290
But aren't you a little late?

00:02:37.290 --> 00:02:39.590
I know, I overslept!

00:02:42.170 --> 00:02:44.550
We heard you're headed for the
Prix de l'Arc de Triomphe.

00:02:44.550 --> 00:02:47.180
Eat some of those, and work hard today!

00:02:47.800 --> 00:02:49.330
Thank you so much!

00:02:49.690 --> 00:02:51.690
The Prix de l'Arc de Triomphe

00:02:50.150 --> 00:02:51.690
And now, a question.

00:02:51.690 --> 00:02:53.840
The highest any Japanese
horse girl has placed in the

00:02:51.690 --> 00:02:56.070
The Prix de l'Arc de Triomphe

00:02:53.840 --> 00:02:55.570
Prix de l'Arc de Triomphe is second.

00:02:55.570 --> 00:03:01.370
The three who have done that are Nakayama
Festa, El Condor Pasa, and who else?

00:03:02.000 --> 00:03:04.200
What exactly was that?

00:03:02.650 --> 00:03:03.670
Kitasan Black.

00:03:05.320 --> 00:03:09.720
I suddenly felt heavy, and my legs didn't
have their usual strength in them...

00:03:10.210 --> 00:03:12.600
Normally, I'd be able to...

00:03:10.210 --> 00:03:12.600
Kitasan Black? Kitasan Black!

00:03:12.600 --> 00:03:14.710
R-Right! Tokai Teio!

00:03:14.710 --> 00:03:17.920
Wrong. The answer is Orfevre.

00:03:18.460 --> 00:03:21.730
This will be important,
so be sure to memorize it.

00:03:24.180 --> 00:03:29.350
You answered Tokai Teio when
the answer was Orfevre?

00:03:29.580 --> 00:03:31.550
Well, I was kind of spacing out.

00:03:31.550 --> 00:03:34.810
I know Dia's gone, but you can't get too lazy!

00:03:34.810 --> 00:03:36.860
You might be right.

00:03:37.490 --> 00:03:39.850
You've got quite an appetite today, Cheval.

00:03:39.850 --> 00:03:41.800
It feels like I can never eat enough.

00:03:41.800 --> 00:03:43.500
Maybe it's a growth spurt?

00:03:43.500 --> 00:03:46.030
I'll be waiting for you at
the Arima Kinen, Kitasan.

00:03:46.870 --> 00:03:51.380
When you get back from the Prix de l'Arc
de Triomphe, I'll have won a G1 title.

00:03:51.380 --> 00:03:52.770
Then we can race at Arima.

00:03:52.770 --> 00:03:53.930
S-Sure.

00:03:53.930 --> 00:03:56.380
I'm not gonna make it easy for you.

00:03:56.640 --> 00:03:59.700
I've finally won a domestic G1 race.

00:03:59.700 --> 00:04:03.610
And I'm aiming to win the Fall Tennoushou,
the Japan Cup, and the Arima Kinen.

00:04:03.610 --> 00:04:05.340
All of them.

00:04:07.760 --> 00:04:09.760
So, when are you flying ou,t Kitasan?

00:04:10.520 --> 00:04:13.410
Uh, I'm still thinking about it.

00:04:13.410 --> 00:04:15.650
Well, make sure you're in
good shape when you do.

00:04:15.980 --> 00:04:18.980
You won't be able to win the Prix de l'Arc
de Triomphe if you run like that again.

00:04:19.650 --> 00:04:22.700
Remember the Takarazuka Kinen?
Did you not train enough?

00:04:23.800 --> 00:04:26.080
Yeah... that might be it.

00:04:27.370 --> 00:04:28.290
Cheval?

00:04:28.290 --> 00:04:29.390
I need seconds.

00:04:29.390 --> 00:04:31.500
Wow, you're still gonna eat?

00:04:33.270 --> 00:04:35.390
If you want, you can have this.

00:04:36.580 --> 00:04:39.210
Oh, you're not eating much today, Kitasan.

00:04:39.210 --> 00:04:41.380
You didn't eat your katsudon dessert.

00:04:41.380 --> 00:04:43.440
I'm just feeling full already.

00:04:43.440 --> 00:04:45.300
Is this because Dia's gone, too?

00:04:45.580 --> 00:04:46.830
Maybe...

00:04:48.280 --> 00:04:51.180
Can this emperor
surpass the last?

00:04:48.280 --> 00:04:51.180
Tokai Teio

00:04:55.180 --> 00:04:57.050
Good morning, Dia-chan.

00:04:58.650 --> 00:04:59.550
Okay.

00:05:13.120 --> 00:05:17.620
Dia-chan

00:05:18.040 --> 00:05:21.700
Dia-chan, just wait. I'll be there soon.

00:05:20.610 --> 00:05:22.670
Bakushin, Bakushin, Bakushin!

00:05:22.670 --> 00:05:24.590
Bakushin, Bakushin, Bakushin!

00:05:24.590 --> 00:05:26.380
Bakushin! Bakushin!

00:05:26.380 --> 00:05:28.720
Baku-shin-shin!

00:05:31.470 --> 00:05:34.890
Don't walk while looking at your phone!

00:05:31.690 --> 00:05:34.890
Sorry! I was looking at
my phone while walking.

00:05:34.890 --> 00:05:37.390
No worries! I should've been more careful too.

00:05:37.390 --> 00:05:39.290
I need to be on my way, though.

00:05:39.290 --> 00:05:40.440
Oh, okay.

00:05:58.080 --> 00:06:00.380
Okay, that was a pretty good time.

00:06:05.530 --> 00:06:07.130
Kita-chan? Something wrong?

00:06:07.130 --> 00:06:09.810
Sorry, I'm gonna run another one.

00:06:22.460 --> 00:06:24.820
Huh? What is going on here?

00:06:25.620 --> 00:06:28.400
Something... something feels...

00:06:29.860 --> 00:06:31.910
Yep, not bad at all, Kitasan.

00:06:34.270 --> 00:06:37.800
Well, I don't think I was able to
pull out all the stops that time.

00:06:37.800 --> 00:06:40.410
But you were able to maintain your time.

00:06:42.880 --> 00:06:45.500
What's wrong? Something feeling different?

00:06:45.840 --> 00:06:47.680
I'm gonna run a bit more.

00:06:47.680 --> 00:06:51.880
Whoa, hold on! If you feel funny,
it's better not to overdo it.

00:06:53.720 --> 00:06:58.670
You might still be exhausted
from the Takarazuka Kinen.

00:06:53.720 --> 00:07:00.640
Goal

00:06:58.670 --> 00:07:00.660
You oughta head back for today and rest up.

00:07:00.660 --> 00:07:01.480
But—

00:07:01.480 --> 00:07:02.380
Kitasan.

00:07:05.650 --> 00:07:08.730
I understand. I'll head on back.

00:07:11.780 --> 00:07:13.020
That girl...

00:07:21.370 --> 00:07:23.810
You did it! That was your best
time today at the end there.

00:07:23.810 --> 00:07:24.830
Yes!

00:07:24.830 --> 00:07:25.790
Here, some water.

00:07:25.790 --> 00:07:27.000
Thank you so much!

00:07:27.480 --> 00:07:29.620
Okay, that ought to do it for today.

00:07:29.620 --> 00:07:30.470
Right!

00:07:30.470 --> 00:07:34.090
Actually, I think I'm gonna do one more lap!

00:07:34.090 --> 00:07:35.560
Your bottle!

00:07:38.090 --> 00:07:41.500
She can still run like that, huh?

00:07:46.900 --> 00:07:48.780
Feeling clean and happy!

00:07:51.530 --> 00:07:53.530
About to have lunch

00:07:56.780 --> 00:07:59.290
Have you decided when you're
coming to France?

00:08:05.790 --> 00:08:09.050
Honestly, Dia-chan,
I'm feeling kinda weird

00:08:17.880 --> 00:08:18.470
Yours now.

00:08:20.000 --> 00:08:22.100
Let's see how many you can put together.

00:08:27.110 --> 00:08:30.110
I'll let you know as soon
as I've got a date. Good night.

00:08:30.110 --> 00:08:30.860
I'll let you know as soon as I've got a date. Good night.

00:08:37.470 --> 00:08:38.600
I'm fine.

00:08:40.560 --> 00:08:42.870
I'm fine. It's fine.

00:08:48.470 --> 00:08:50.160
I'm sure it's okay.

00:08:51.270 --> 00:08:56.400
I'll get a lot of sleep, eat my fill,
and get into proper shape.

00:08:57.390 --> 00:09:00.910
If I practice... If I practice
a whole bunch, I'm sure—

00:09:01.230 --> 00:09:04.610
"If I practice enough, I can go
back to being the way I used to be."

00:09:07.410 --> 00:09:08.590
Golshi-san...

00:09:09.230 --> 00:09:12.070
But... it ain't like that.

00:09:12.070 --> 00:09:14.650
No matter how hard you practice.
No matter what you do.

00:09:15.160 --> 00:09:16.230
How'd you...

00:09:16.230 --> 00:09:18.530
Because I've been through the same thing.

00:09:20.110 --> 00:09:23.130
At some point, I couldn't pass
anyone the way I used to.

00:09:23.830 --> 00:09:26.810
I started having trouble
controlling my emotions.

00:09:27.150 --> 00:09:29.130
Got bad at exiting the gate, too.

00:09:31.770 --> 00:09:33.050
Kitasan Black...

00:09:34.500 --> 00:09:37.340
You're past your peak.

00:09:42.100 --> 00:09:42.600
Honestly, Dia-chan,
I'm feeling kinda weird

00:09:45.230 --> 00:09:45.980
Honestly, Dia-chan,
I'm feeling kinda weird

00:09:52.980 --> 00:09:56.990
Umamusume

00:09:52.980 --> 00:09:56.990
Pretty Derby

00:10:00.660 --> 00:10:02.250
I... see.

00:10:03.200 --> 00:10:05.530
I had hoped that wasn't the case.

00:10:06.250 --> 00:10:09.440
So, back at the Takarazuka Kinen...

00:10:09.440 --> 00:10:10.570
Trainer-san...

00:10:11.250 --> 00:10:14.940
I can keep running, can't I?

00:10:16.830 --> 00:10:19.130
Of course, being past your prime doesn't mean

00:10:19.130 --> 00:10:21.600
that you'll suddenly stop being able to race.

00:10:21.600 --> 00:10:25.430
But it is true that you'll be
less competitive over time.

00:10:26.330 --> 00:10:28.830
How long do I have?

00:10:28.830 --> 00:10:31.940
When it come to horse girls
who have passed their peak...

00:10:31.940 --> 00:10:34.690
It can play out any number of ways.

00:10:34.910 --> 00:10:38.070
Some are suddenly unable
to run at all anymore,

00:10:38.070 --> 00:10:40.820
and some see a gradual
decline in their ability.

00:10:41.250 --> 00:10:43.270
There've been a few who suddenly
became competitive again,

00:10:43.270 --> 00:10:45.210
like they were reborn, but...

00:10:45.640 --> 00:10:46.590
In that case...

00:10:46.590 --> 00:10:50.080
In that case, I might be
able to keep running, right?

00:10:51.230 --> 00:10:52.390
It's possible.

00:10:54.900 --> 00:10:57.530
But... what about the Prix
de l'Arc de Triomphe?

00:10:58.720 --> 00:11:03.440
It's a goal that many horse girls
have attempted and failed at.

00:11:03.840 --> 00:11:09.980
If you do win there, you'd leave your
mark on Japanese horse girl history.

00:11:09.980 --> 00:11:11.970
But you'd be traveling a huge distance,

00:11:11.970 --> 00:11:13.670
dealing with compatibility
issues with overseas turf,

00:11:13.670 --> 00:11:16.440
and facing a whole slew of other risks.

00:11:17.700 --> 00:11:21.420
Whatever you decide... make sure
you don't have any regrets.

00:11:23.170 --> 00:11:25.930
I understand. If you'll excuse me.

00:11:29.850 --> 00:11:31.160
To be honest...

00:11:32.300 --> 00:11:35.160
I wouldn't want you to go in your condition.

00:11:43.800 --> 00:11:45.800
Fukunaga Shopping District

00:11:46.730 --> 00:11:48.580
I'm past my peak...

00:11:48.580 --> 00:11:50.650
So that's what it was.

00:11:51.730 --> 00:11:56.760
What do I do? What do I do? What do I do?

00:11:57.910 --> 00:12:00.170
Dia-chan, I...

00:12:00.170 --> 00:12:01.850
Okay, it's all done!

00:12:03.320 --> 00:12:04.830
Looks about right.

00:12:04.250 --> 00:12:05.320
It's lovely!

00:12:04.830 --> 00:12:05.320
Hold it open...

00:12:05.530 --> 00:12:06.560
Lift it up! A bit higher!

00:12:06.560 --> 00:12:07.830
Easy there...

00:12:09.870 --> 00:12:10.830
Nice!

00:12:10.610 --> 00:12:12.190
It is.

00:12:10.830 --> 00:12:14.830
The Prix de l'Arc de Triomphe!!
It's a festival!! Kitasan Black!!

00:12:12.190 --> 00:12:13.270
Wow, it's huge!

00:12:13.270 --> 00:12:14.830
It turned out great, though.

00:12:15.210 --> 00:12:17.730
Thank you all so much for helping with it.

00:12:17.730 --> 00:12:19.970
Come on, it was our pleasure!

00:12:19.970 --> 00:12:22.380
It really is a wonderful flag.

00:12:22.380 --> 00:12:24.650
Our Kita-chan running at the
Prix de l'Arc de Triomphe...

00:12:24.650 --> 00:12:26.700
Sounds like something from a dream.

00:12:27.290 --> 00:12:28.610
The thing is...

00:12:29.100 --> 00:12:32.520
Look, I know it'd be amazing for
her to race in France, right?

00:12:33.120 --> 00:12:34.440
But still...

00:12:34.440 --> 00:12:38.190
I think running in Fuchu
suits her best of all.

00:12:38.190 --> 00:12:39.690
You've got a point.

00:12:39.690 --> 00:12:43.530
I was hoping to root for her in the
stands during the fall G1 races.

00:12:43.530 --> 00:12:45.140
It would've been great

00:12:45.140 --> 00:12:47.870
if we could all watch Kita-chan
win both Tennoushous in one year!

00:12:48.160 --> 00:12:51.130
We won't be able to see
her for a while, will we?

00:12:51.130 --> 00:12:52.620
I'll miss her.

00:12:52.620 --> 00:12:56.180
Passing a banana to Kita-chan
when she runs by every morning,

00:12:56.180 --> 00:12:59.690
and then at the end of the
week following her races...

00:12:59.690 --> 00:13:03.370
She's become a part of our
daily lives, hasn't she?

00:13:05.880 --> 00:13:08.390
The Prix de l'Arc de Triomphe!!
It's a festival!! Kitasan Black!!

00:13:12.640 --> 00:13:14.640
Trainer's Office

00:13:15.020 --> 00:13:17.420
I see... so you've decided.

00:13:17.420 --> 00:13:18.180
Right.

00:13:19.210 --> 00:13:24.150
They want to watch me. To watch me race.

00:13:24.620 --> 00:13:30.020
They said that I'm part of it.
Part of their daily lives.

00:13:30.820 --> 00:13:33.620
So I'm not going to France.

00:13:35.860 --> 00:13:38.720
If I've only got a limited
amount of time left...

00:13:38.720 --> 00:13:43.000
I want all of my races to be in front of
the people who are cheering for me.

00:13:43.000 --> 00:13:44.100
Kitasan...

00:13:44.510 --> 00:13:47.670
So register me for a whole
bunch of races, please!

00:13:47.670 --> 00:13:52.410
The Fall Tennoushou, the Japan Cup,
the Arima Kinen... I'll run in them all.

00:13:52.410 --> 00:13:55.680
Maybe you'll try for the Fall
Senior Triple Crown, then.

00:13:56.230 --> 00:13:59.850
There've only been two horse
girls who've managed to win

00:13:59.850 --> 00:14:01.770
those three particular G1 races.

00:14:01.770 --> 00:14:06.940
Plus, the Fall Tennoushou is your chance to
win both of those races in a single year.

00:14:06.940 --> 00:14:07.650
How about it?

00:14:08.200 --> 00:14:09.050
Yeah!

00:14:09.530 --> 00:14:13.130
Okay, in that case,
the Fall Tennoushou comes first.

00:14:13.130 --> 00:14:14.180
Trainer-san.

00:14:14.180 --> 00:14:18.580
I'm going to win the Tennoushou to
prove that I can still keep running.

00:14:19.530 --> 00:14:20.340
Sure.

00:14:20.830 --> 00:14:24.090
Okay! Let's do this!

00:14:25.610 --> 00:14:26.590
Yeah...

00:14:27.070 --> 00:14:29.670
I'm sorry I can't run with you.

00:14:30.490 --> 00:14:33.100
Yeah... Yeah.

00:14:33.410 --> 00:14:34.790
Let's both do our best.

00:14:35.370 --> 00:14:36.400
Bye.

00:14:48.950 --> 00:14:51.450
Kitasan Black's Prix de l'Arc
de Triomphe Plans Canceled

00:14:51.450 --> 00:14:53.950
Kitasan Black's Prix de l'Arc
de Triomphe Plans Canceled

00:15:39.370 --> 00:15:42.620
Satono Diamond Places 15th at
the Prix de l'Arc de Triomphe

00:16:05.200 --> 00:16:07.610
We're seeing a sky darkened
by a passing typhoon,

00:16:08.500 --> 00:16:11.040
with heavy turf as a result
of persistent rain.

00:16:11.040 --> 00:16:12.530
And in spite of that,

00:16:12.530 --> 00:16:16.580
the bleachers here at the Tokyo Racecourse

00:16:16.580 --> 00:16:18.540
are full of fans who've
gathered to watch them race.

00:16:18.750 --> 00:16:23.290
We've got an impressive lineup of eight
G1 horse girls competing today...

00:16:23.290 --> 00:16:27.030
And the most attention arguably falls on
Kitasan Black, with five G1 wins currently.

00:16:27.030 --> 00:16:27.790
That's right.

00:16:27.790 --> 00:16:29.450
If she can get out in front as usual,

00:16:29.450 --> 00:16:31.800
we're likely to see an
impressive race from her.

00:16:31.800 --> 00:16:35.010
What about Satono Crown,
who won the Takarazuka Kinen?

00:16:35.010 --> 00:16:37.300
She's shown a knack for
running on heavy turf before.

00:16:37.300 --> 00:16:40.780
It'll be interesting to see how
that plays into today's race.

00:16:41.800 --> 00:16:44.840
The Fall Tennoushou will be starting shortly.

00:17:07.600 --> 00:17:11.050
The Fall Tennoushou—2,000 meters in the rain—

00:17:12.720 --> 00:17:14.310
has begun!

00:17:14.310 --> 00:17:17.400
Whoa, and it looks like Kitasan
Black has made a late start!

00:17:17.400 --> 00:17:18.800
She's running late!

00:17:18.800 --> 00:17:21.370
We're seeing an intense fight for
first place in the muddy turf.

00:17:21.370 --> 00:17:23.340
The rain may have thrown her timing off,

00:17:23.340 --> 00:17:26.410
because Kitasan Black
is off to a rough start!

00:17:26.410 --> 00:17:29.370
She's going to be observing the race
from the rear to start off today!

00:17:29.370 --> 00:17:30.870
Kita-san had a late start?!

00:17:30.870 --> 00:17:33.230
This doesn't look good.

00:17:33.750 --> 00:17:37.490
And in the first corner, we're seeing
number 11, Tour d’Ivoire,

00:17:37.490 --> 00:17:40.880
number one, Hard Control, and
Kitasan Black in these positions!

00:17:41.740 --> 00:17:43.900
The Fall Tennoushou is said to be
the traditional way of determining

00:17:43.900 --> 00:17:45.610
who among the senior class running classic races

00:17:45.610 --> 00:17:46.580
is the best at medium distances.

00:17:46.580 --> 00:17:47.690
What brought that on?

00:17:47.690 --> 00:17:48.390
In this race,

00:17:48.390 --> 00:17:50.950
the first time you hit the second corner
is relatively short at 100 meters.

00:17:50.950 --> 00:17:52.470
They say running on the inside is advantageous,

00:17:52.470 --> 00:17:54.800
but considering the typhoon has
turned the turf heavy and muddy...

00:17:54.800 --> 00:17:56.480
The runners avoid rough
patches on the inner edge,

00:17:56.480 --> 00:17:58.430
causing more crowd density in the corner,

00:17:58.430 --> 00:18:00.260
which has made a mess of
the fight for the lead.

00:18:00.260 --> 00:18:02.490
And that's gonna make it even
harder for Kitasan Black,

00:18:02.490 --> 00:18:03.810
who started late after a gate bump.

00:18:03.810 --> 00:18:05.950
This is gonna be one tough race.

00:18:05.950 --> 00:18:07.440
I'm amazed you caught all that.

00:18:07.440 --> 00:18:09.380
They've entered the opposite straight.

00:18:09.380 --> 00:18:11.270
Tour d’Ivoire is in the lead.

00:18:11.270 --> 00:18:15.940
On the outside is number 18, Xbalanque,
with Satono Crown moving up on the inside!

00:18:16.180 --> 00:18:18.010
They've cleared the first 1,000 meters.

00:18:18.010 --> 00:18:21.430
The rough turf is clearly having
an effect, as it took 64 seconds.

00:18:25.540 --> 00:18:27.810
Everyone's having such a hard time.

00:18:27.810 --> 00:18:29.830
With the turf in this condition...

00:18:29.830 --> 00:18:34.710
Trouble like this wouldn't normally
be enough to slow Kitasan down.

00:18:34.710 --> 00:18:37.120
They're now entering the third curve.

00:18:37.120 --> 00:18:41.360
Tour d’Ivoire is still in the lead...
Wait, it looks like Faster Than Ray has it now!

00:18:43.050 --> 00:18:43.790
Okay!

00:18:49.030 --> 00:18:50.080
Kitasan?!

00:18:51.130 --> 00:18:53.060
Where's this intensity coming from?

00:18:53.060 --> 00:18:54.990
I can't lose... I won't!

00:18:55.580 --> 00:18:58.560
And now Satono Crown has
risen to second place!

00:18:58.560 --> 00:19:00.360
Which one of these horse girls

00:19:00.360 --> 00:19:02.960
will conquer this muddy track
to claim the autumn plaque?!

00:19:02.960 --> 00:19:05.970
And now, entering the final corner,
with less than 600 meters left!

00:19:05.970 --> 00:19:08.410
The horse girls are beginning
their last spurt!

00:19:08.410 --> 00:19:10.340
They're avoiding the track's inside,
a slushy mess,

00:19:10.340 --> 00:19:12.170
and running on the outside!

00:19:12.170 --> 00:19:14.220
And Faster Than Ray is in first place!

00:19:14.220 --> 00:19:16.560
It looks like this course has taken
its toll on the G1 horse girls,

00:19:16.560 --> 00:19:19.150
because no one is closing in!

00:19:19.670 --> 00:19:20.800
Whoa there!

00:19:20.800 --> 00:19:23.000
And it's Satono Crown who
starts to push forward!

00:19:23.000 --> 00:19:26.690
She's proving her skill at running
through mud as she starts to move up!

00:19:26.690 --> 00:19:27.550
Okay!

00:19:27.550 --> 00:19:29.930
Satono Crown seizes the lead—

00:19:29.930 --> 00:19:33.980
No, and now, all of a sudden,
here's Kitasan Black!

00:19:35.360 --> 00:19:36.590
She's charging her way through

00:19:36.590 --> 00:19:39.000
the muddy inside of the track
that everyone is avoiding,

00:19:39.000 --> 00:19:41.510
and Kitasan Black is suddenly gaining ground!

00:19:43.220 --> 00:19:44.230
Crown-san!

00:19:44.230 --> 00:19:45.740
Go!

00:19:45.740 --> 00:19:47.370
Do it! Kitasan!

00:19:47.370 --> 00:19:49.360
Kitasan Black is furiously closing in!

00:19:49.360 --> 00:19:51.120
And now she's in the lead!

00:19:52.920 --> 00:19:54.880
I'm gonna win this!

00:19:54.880 --> 00:19:56.580
Four hundred meters to go!

00:19:56.580 --> 00:19:58.500
Kitasan is maintaining her lead!
She's still ahead!

00:19:58.500 --> 00:19:59.880
But Satono Crown is right behind!

00:20:00.130 --> 00:20:01.880
Can Kitasan Black escape her?!

00:20:01.880 --> 00:20:03.790
Can Satono Crown pass her?!

00:20:05.510 --> 00:20:06.390
Kitasan!

00:20:07.070 --> 00:20:08.050
This is it!

00:20:10.500 --> 00:20:12.010
Kitasan is looking strained!

00:20:12.010 --> 00:20:14.980
And now Satono Crown moves to
the inside in an effort to pass!

00:20:14.980 --> 00:20:16.980
Here comes Crown! Here comes Crown!

00:20:16.980 --> 00:20:17.890
The gap is shrinking!

00:20:17.890 --> 00:20:19.980
Kitasan is holding on for
dear life! She's still in the lead!

00:20:19.980 --> 00:20:21.970
We're seeing a real struggle
through this muddy terrain

00:20:21.970 --> 00:20:24.750
as they both push forward down the lengthy

00:20:24.750 --> 00:20:26.620
Tokyo straight towards glory in a dead heat!

00:20:26.620 --> 00:20:29.410
Who will obtain the fall plaque
in the middle of this storm?!

00:20:29.410 --> 00:20:33.000
Kitasan Black?! Or Satono Crown?!

00:20:33.000 --> 00:20:34.830
Crown-san! You can do it!

00:20:34.830 --> 00:20:36.380
Go!

00:20:44.160 --> 00:20:45.900
But Kitasan holds!

00:20:45.900 --> 00:20:47.390
It's Kitasan Black!

00:20:47.390 --> 00:20:50.220
And Kitasan Black crosses the goal!

00:20:50.890 --> 00:20:53.530
The anxieties from the Arima
Kinen have been laid to rest!

00:20:53.530 --> 00:20:55.770
What a splendid win from Kitasan Black!

00:20:55.770 --> 00:20:57.240
She had a rare slip up at the start,

00:20:57.240 --> 00:20:59.810
but when all was said
and done, it wasn't a problem!

00:20:59.810 --> 00:21:02.750
She was able to overpower
the typhoon-muddied course,

00:21:02.750 --> 00:21:07.660
and demonstrate why she's currently
considered the strongest in the Twinkle Series!

00:21:07.660 --> 00:21:10.260
By winning the Fall Tennoushou!

00:21:10.690 --> 00:21:14.620
And with that, she has won both
Tennoushou races in a single year!

00:21:14.070 --> 00:21:17.150
Amazing... Kita-san was really amazing!

00:21:14.650 --> 00:21:17.400
In addition to Special Week and T.M. Opera O,

00:21:17.400 --> 00:21:22.300
we've seen Kitasan Black's name
chiseled into horse girl history!

00:21:22.300 --> 00:21:25.300
A winning time of 02:08.30!

00:21:25.300 --> 00:21:27.720
She was able to overcome
some rough conditions,

00:21:27.720 --> 00:21:32.340
and keep Satono Crown from managing
to get ahead until the end!

00:21:32.340 --> 00:21:35.580
Kitasan Black has now won
her sixth G1 victory!

00:22:01.170 --> 00:22:02.650
I see...

00:22:06.820 --> 00:22:07.970
I see.

00:22:11.530 --> 00:22:13.210
I see...

00:22:14.305 --> 00:23:14.175
